public abstract class MetaParameter
extends Parameter
implements java.util.Observer

A MetaParameter is an abstract class that represents a parameter value that is somewhat dynamic. A meta parameter is not a value retreived diretly from the ECU. Instead, it's a parameter that can have special operations done on it's value before returned to observer. The best example is the MetaParameter.
